summary: I think for some people it's not about worrying about her age, but just being disappointed knowing that we won't see an older...
question: I think for some people it's not about worrying about her age, but just being disappointed knowing that we won't see an older Carol at any point. I LOVE Brie Larson and she's clearly going to do an amazing job, but I can't help wishing they would have taken the chance to cast actress in 40s for Carol. I'm almost 26 though so I might just feel more biased about wanting to see more actresses over 30 and 40 because I'm sad and anxious about being an aging woman myself.
answer:
There was some debate on Brie being too young for the role, but she’s 28 and Carol was 29 (I think) around the time she lost her memories in the comics because of Rogue so her age is right. And Brie is so amazing… we’re all gonna love her!

I agree we need more older women being badass, though.
